messages.messageBody:
HAPPY VALENTINE'S DAY!!!!

This is the last Call to save money on registration!
Registration prices go up on Monday!  If you haven't registered
yet, don't wait!  Discounted Registration prices are only
available until tomorrow, February 15!!  Kids are still the
same low price they always are, but adult and family regular
prices are reduced as it makes our job so much easier if we can
get your Name Tags created and ready well before the conference.
Register now at
[http://www.hena.us/conferenceRegistration.html%5d!

New speakers have been added, so keep checking our Schedule at
http://www.hena.us/conferenceSchedule.html
[http://www.hena.us/ConferenceSchedule.html%5d and our speaker list
at [http://www.hena.us/conferenceSpeaker.html%5d!  Keep checking
back!

KIDS ACTIVITIES - TALENT SHOW - KIDS THEATER PRODUCTION - FUN!

Remember to bring your Game Cube Games and PS2 games as we will
have those systems available again in the video game room!
You're welcome to bring your laptop as well since there is free
wireless internet throughout ASU.   There will also be a bone
box, dancing, planting actives from Desert Botanical Gardens,
board games, movies and a young kids room as well as BINGO,
Bowling, the Homeschool Theatre presentation of Aladdin and our
annual Talent Show for all ages!  All of this is included in
your one low registration fee!

If you are homeschooling or just curious about homeschooling
DON'T MISS THIS EVENT! We are open to all and support families
that homeschool and children are welcome! Please feel free to
forward this notice!

Register now at:  [http://hena.us/conferenceRegistration.html%5d

As always, volunteers are free, so if you want to volunteer,
please contact us and let us know!  We still have a few openings.

We look forward to seeing you at the HENA 2009 conference on
March 7, 2009 at ASU Memorial Union in Tempe!

Cindy Fox
HENA 2009 Conference Coordinator
[http://www.hena.us/conference.html%5d
602-692-8923

The Home Education Network of Arizona is an inclusive statewide
support organization that respects, values, and finds strength
in diversity. We are neutral in matters of religion and partisan
politics and we respect each other's educational choices. HENA's
mission is to create an environment in which all home educating
families in Arizona can share resources, find support, and build
community.
